# UI

## Design-first

Complete the Figma page (see `docs/design/figma/`) before implementing a screen.

## Colors

Use **only** tokens from `AppColors` and `context.semanticColors`.
Never use `Colors.*`, hex literals, or `Color(0x...)` in widgets.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
color: AppColors.primary
color: context.semanticColors.success

// ❌ BAD
color: Colors.blue
color: Color(0xFF2563EB)
```

## Typography

Use `Theme.of(context).textTheme` (Display, Headline, Title, Body, Label) or `AppTypography.caption`.
Never hardcode `fontSize` or `fontWeight` in widgets.

## Responsive

Use `Breakpoints` and `context.responsive()` / `ResponsiveBuilder` / `ResponsiveContainer`.
Never hardcode pixel widths (`width: 375`).

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
padding: EdgeInsets.symmetric(horizontal: context.horizontalPadding)

// ❌ BAD
SizedBox(width: 360, child: ...)
```

## Structure

- Pages in `presentation/pages/`; feature widgets in `presentation/widgets/`.
- Keep widgets thin — business logic lives in Bloc.
- Use `BlocBuilder` / `BlocListener`; no direct repository calls from UI.
